import TNLean.MPS.MPDO.AreaLaw
import TNLean.MPS.RFP.Defs

/-!
# Purification renormalization fixed point (PRFP)

This file formalizes the **purification renormalization fixed point** predicate
for matrix product density operators, following arXiv:1606.00608
(Cirac–Pérez-García–Schuch–Verstraete), Definition 4.4 (`def:Puri-RFP`,
lines 756–764).

A tensor `M` generating MPDOs need not be a renormalization fixed point in the
transfer-map sense; instead, when `M` has a *purification*, one writes `M`
through a pure MPS tensor `A` whose physical leg carries both the spin and an
ancillary index. The MPDO is recovered by tracing out the ancillas:

  `ρ^{(N)}_p(M) = tr_a(|Ψ^{(N)}(A)⟩⟨Ψ^{(N)}(A)|)`     (eq:MPDO-Puri-1, line 757)

The tensor `M` is a **PRFP** when such a purification exists with `A` a pure-state
renormalization fixed point (`MPSTensor.IsRFP`, arXiv:1606.00608, Definition 3.2).

## Faithfulness note

This restates Definition 4.4 with the *global purification equation*
(eq:MPDO-Puri-1) as the defining condition: every system size `N` of the MPDO is
the partial trace over the per-site ancillas of the pure state generated by `A`.
The earlier `IsPRFP` (removed in #2386) kept only a local witness plus generic
transfer-map idempotence of the purifying tensor, dropping eq:MPDO-Puri-1; with
that weaker hypothesis `IsPRFP → IsZCL` had a machine-checked
counterexample, contradicting the source's stated equivalence (line 777). The
deviation is documented in
`docs/paper-gaps/cpsv16_purification_rfp_definition.tex`.

The source equivalence `IsPRFP ↔ IsZCL` (Theorem line 777, statements (i)⟺(ii))
needs the *tensor-level* purification relation `M^{ij} = ∑ₖ A^{(i,k)} ⊗ A^{(j,k)*}`
to compare transfer maps; with only the state-level equation here, the forward
implication is tracked as follow-up. The provable faithfulness check supplied
below is `IsPRFP M → IsMPDO M`: a purified tensor genuinely generates MPDOs.

## Main definitions

* `ancillaSplitEquiv`: the per-site identification
  `(Fin N → Fin (d * da)) ≃ (Fin N → Fin d) × (Fin N → Fin da)` splitting each
  physical leg into its spin and ancilla parts.
* `ancillaPartialTrace`: tracing out the per-site ancillas of a state on the
  combined spin–ancilla chain.
* `MPOTensor.IsPRFP`: the purification renormalization fixed-point predicate.

## Main results

* `MPOTensor.IsPRFP.isMPDO`: a PRFP tensor generates MPDOs.

## References

* [Cirac--Perez-Garcia--Schuch--Verstraete 2017] arXiv:1606.00608,
  Definition 4.4 (`def:Puri-RFP`, lines 756–764), eq:MPDO-Puri-1 (line 757),
  Theorem (line 777).
-/

open scoped Matrix ComplexOrder
open Matrix

/-! ## Per-site ancilla partial trace -/

/-- The per-site identification splitting a configuration on `N` spin–ancilla
legs into its spin and ancilla parts:
`(Fin N → Fin (d * da)) ≃ (Fin N → Fin d) × (Fin N → Fin da)`. -/
def ancillaSplitEquiv (d da N : ℕ) :
    (Fin N → Fin (d * da)) ≃ (Fin N → Fin d) × (Fin N → Fin da) :=
  (Equiv.arrowCongr (Equiv.refl (Fin N)) finProdFinEquiv.symm).trans
    (Equiv.arrowProdEquivProdArrow (Fin N) (fun _ => Fin d) (fun _ => Fin da))

/-- Tracing out the per-site ancillas of a state on the combined spin–ancilla
chain `(Fin N → Fin (d * da))`, leaving a state on the spin chain
`(Fin N → Fin d)`. This is `tr_a` of eq:MPDO-Puri-1. -/
noncomputable def ancillaPartialTrace (d da N : ℕ)
    (ρ : Matrix (Fin N → Fin (d * da)) (Fin N → Fin (d * da)) ℂ) :
    Matrix (Fin N → Fin d) (Fin N → Fin d) ℂ :=
  Matrix.partialTraceRight
    (ρ.submatrix (ancillaSplitEquiv d da N).symm (ancillaSplitEquiv d da N).symm)

/-- The ancilla partial trace of a positive semidefinite state is positive
semidefinite. -/
theorem ancillaPartialTrace_posSemidef {d da N : ℕ}
    {ρ : Matrix (Fin N → Fin (d * da)) (Fin N → Fin (d * da)) ℂ}
    (hρ : ρ.PosSemidef) : (ancillaPartialTrace d da N ρ).PosSemidef :=
  (hρ.submatrix _).partialTraceRight

namespace MPOTensor

variable {d D : ℕ}

/-- A tensor `M` is a **purification renormalization fixed point** (PRFP) when it
admits a purification by a pure-state renormalization fixed point: there is a
spin–ancilla MPS tensor `A` with `A.IsRFP` such that, for every system size `N`,
the MPDO `ρ^{(N)}_p(M)` equals the partial trace over the ancillas of the pure
state generated by `A`:

  `ρ^{(N)}_p(M) = tr_a(|Ψ^{(N)}(A)⟩⟨Ψ^{(N)}(A)|)`.

Source: arXiv:1606.00608, Definition 4.4 (`def:Puri-RFP`, lines 756–764),
eq:MPDO-Puri-1 (line 757). -/
def IsPRFP (M : MPOTensor d D) : Prop :=
  ∃ (da Da : ℕ) (A : MPSTensor (d * da) Da),
    A.IsRFP ∧ ∀ N : ℕ, mpo M N = ancillaPartialTrace d da N (A.pureState N)

/-- A purification renormalization fixed point generates matrix product density
operators: tracing the ancillas of a (positive semidefinite) pure state yields a
positive semidefinite operator at every system size. This is the provable
faithfulness check on `IsPRFP` (cf. the equivalence with ZCL, line 777). -/
theorem IsPRFP.isMPDO {M : MPOTensor d D} (h : IsPRFP M) : IsMPDO M := by
  obtain ⟨da, Da, A, _, hpuri⟩ := h
  intro N
  rw [hpuri N]
  exact ancillaPartialTrace_posSemidef (A.pureState_posSemidef N)

end MPOTensor
